data.title: Jill Scott: : Directory: About: School of Education: Indiana University Bloomington
data.text: Jill Scott has served as an elementary teacher, literacy coach, elementary field supervisor, and most recently as an Associate Instructor teaching core literacy courses across three programs: Elementary Education, Early Childhood Education, and Special Education/Elementary Education. Jill has taught Methods of Teaching Reading and Language Arts, Early Literacy and Play-Based Instruction, Reading Research for Literacy Leaders, and Instructional Issues in Language Arts for Literacy Teachers. She is expected to earn her Ph.D. in Literacy, Culture, and Language Education from Indiana University Bloomington in October 2023.
